 that \u2018the term \u201cindividualism\u201d causes trouble\u2019 and that \u2018contemporary scholars who deem it wholly negative, use it as an archetype, or use it to symbolize Western modernity\u2026 [which leads] into overlooking what data show\u2019 (Brown, \u2018Is Buddhism\u2019, 89). Our approach may be taken as a confirmation of Brown\u2019s point: regardless of whether and in which sense Theravada doctrine and practice is \u2018individualist\u2019, it informs \u2018non-individualistic\u2019 beliefs and habituates virtues such as those characteristic of VHVs."
